Cookie:<br><br>
It feels strange to sit here and have compassion for a former enemy.  I can equate the damage of a hurricane to human suffering...loss of property..loss of loved ones..etc.<br>
I feel genuine sorrow for those people.  Still remember a little Vietnamese girl scrutinizing my Comanche features and saying, &quot;You same same me.&quot;<br><br>
Hurricanes and war seem to have some things in common... they are sudden...tragic..senseless, but they will always be there.. and they seem to cause the greatest impact upon the poor.<br><br>
I stay close to the TV when tornadoes are bouncing around in Oklahoma.  Doppler radar and other sophisticated weather forecasting helps issue warnings and predict the paths of violent storms.  Probably, these folks had no warning.<br><br>
Problem is.. some people don't pay heed to the warnings.. for pending storms or war.<br><br>
Thanks for the postings.<br><br>
